New Stuff

	2.06:
	Hdrtag now supports etags-style tagging.  Using the -e option, it creats
	<hdrtags> using an almost-etags style; "flist -me" will finish the job,
	creating a <TAGS> file.

	Hdrtag now also supports *.y (yacc, bison) files, tagging productions,
	%left/%right operators, %types, etc.

	Hdrtag now prioritizes tags internally: typedefs have high priority,
	prototypes have low priority, etc.  Prioritization affects the order
	that (ctags-style) tags will appear; excluding duplicates (the default
	behavior) will cause only the highest priority tag to be retained.

	Bugs have been squashed, of course.
